abstract: A bitterly divided U.S. House of Representatives engaged in an impeachment debate before historic votes on two charges accusing President Donald Trump of abusing his power and obstructing Congress.
snippet: A bitterly divided U.S. House of Representatives engaged in an impeachment debate before historic votes on two charges accusing President Donald Trump of abusing his power and obstructing Congress.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A bitterly divided U.S. House of Representatives engaged in an impeachment debate before historic votes on two charges accusing President Donald Trump of abusing his power and obstructing Congress.
headline_main: 'Civics Lesson' or 'Sham Trial?' Key Moments in the House Impeachment Debate
headline_print_headline: 'Civics Lesson' or 'Sham Trial?' Key Moments in the House Impeachment Debate

abstract: With the UK election results giving some certainty to the Brexit process, a U.S.-China trade deal all but signed and the Federal Reserve signaling that it will stand steady for the foreseeable future, there are three fewer hurdles standing in the way of global equities extending their record run into 2020.
snippet: With the UK election results giving some certainty to the Brexit process, a U.S.-China trade deal all but signed and the Federal Reserve signaling that it will stand steady for the foreseeable future, there are three fewer hurdles standing in the ...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — With the UK election results giving some certainty to the Brexit process, a U.S.-China trade deal all but signed and the Federal Reserve signaling that it will stand steady for the foreseeable future, there are three fewer hurdles standing in the way of global equities extending their record run into 2020.
headline_main: Where's the Risk? U.S. Fund Managers Bet on Bull Run in 2020
headline_print_headline: Where's the Risk? U.S. Fund Managers Bet on Bull Run in 2020

abstract: Democrats never gave Bill Clinton a free pass. Why are Republicans giving one to Donald Trump?
snippet: Democrats never gave Bill Clinton a free pass. Why are Republicans giving one to Donald Trump?
lead_paragraph: Update: On Wednesday, the House of Representatives voted to impeach President Trump for abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.

headline_main: The Republican Party Is Completely Behind President Trump

abstract: Republicans of courage and conscience ought to join the Democrats who cast their votes for impeachment.
snippet: Republicans of courage and conscience ought to join the Democrats who cast their votes for impeachment.
lead_paragraph: When the framers of our Constitution laid out the process of impeachment in 1787, they could hardly imagine the circumstances that brought us to this week’s vote in the House. With the combination of a telephone call soliciting foreign interference in our election, the hiding of that call’s summary on a special computer server and a barrage of presidential tweets denying any quid pro quo, it’s easy to imagine Alexander Hamilton, James Madison and John Jay scratching their heads.

abstract: Speaker Nancy Pelosi wants to be remembered for her legislative accomplishments, like passing the Affordable Care Act. But her legacy is now tied to the impeachment of the 45th president.
snippet: Speaker Nancy Pelosi wants to be remembered for her legislative accomplishments, like passing the Affordable Care Act. But her legacy is now tied to the impeachment of the 45th president.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Hours before she announced the House would investigate whether to impeach President Trump, Speaker Nancy Pelosi received a call from him at her Washington home, ostensibly to talk about gun violence. But he quickly changed the topic to Ukraine.

abstract: Arsenal's Mesut Ozil has been removed from Konami's eFootball Pro Evolution Soccer (PES) 2020 computer game in China over his comments about the country's treatment of its Uighur Muslims.
snippet: Arsenal's Mesut Ozil has been removed from Konami's eFootball Pro Evolution Soccer (PES) 2020 computer game in China over his comments about the country's treatment of its Uighur Muslims.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Arsenal's Mesut Ozil has been removed from Konami's eFootball Pro Evolution Soccer (PES) 2020 computer game in China over his comments about the country's treatment of its Uighur Muslims.
headline_main: Ozil Removed From Computer Game in China Over Uighur Comments

abstract: Immigrants convicted of illegally reentering the U.S., driving drunk or committing domestic violence will be barred from claiming asylum under a proposed regulation announced Wednesday by the Trump administration.
snippet: Immigrants convicted of illegally reentering the U.S., driving drunk or committing domestic violence will be barred from claiming asylum under a proposed regulation announced Wednesday by the Trump administration.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Immigrants convicted of illegally reentering the U.S., driving drunk or committing domestic violence will be barred from claiming asylum under a proposed regulation announced Wednesday by the Trump administration.
headline_main: Administration Seeks to Bar Convicted Immigrants From Asylum
headline_print_headline: Administration Seeks to Bar Convicted Immigrants From Asylum
